    "If we simply ignore the ability to answer said questions, all we could say is that any agent that cannot reason counterfactually has no understanding.",
    "What-questions ask for descriptive knowledge about an object or phenomenon (Belnap & Steel, 1976; Cross & Roelofsen, 2022).",
    "Answering such questions requires having access to information, whether from memory or external sources (books, servers, etc.).",
    "What-questions can ask for values, dimensions, or names, among other things.",
    "For example, what is the charge of the electron?"
